        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38457",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mondaine",
                        "name": "mondaine",
                        "displayName": "Max Mondaine",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I have the same problem, I upgraded from 1.10 to 1.10.1. I just replaced the library\/Zend folder and get many error like this:\r\n\r\nfunction.is-readable]: open_basedir restriction in effect. File(\/usr\/share\/php\/My\/Helper\/BaseUrl.php) is not within the allowed path(s): (\/var\/www\/clients\/client4\/web39) in \/var\/www\/clients\/client4\/web39\/gui\/library\/Zend\/Loader.php on line 190\r\n\r\nWarning: is_readable() [function.is-readable]: open_basedir restriction in effect. File(\/usr\/share\/pear\/My\/Helper\/BaseUrl.php) is not within the allowed path(s): (\/var\/www\/clients\/client4\/web39) in \/var\/www\/clients\/client4\/web39\/gui\/library\/Zend\/Loader.php on line 190\r\n\r\nI use custom view helper and decorator which worked fine in 1.10.\r\nI can't find any place where I add '\/usr\/share\/php' to my path.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mondaine",
                        "name": "mondaine",
                        "displayName": "Max Mondaine",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-15T06:01:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-15T06:01:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38458",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "open_basedir limits you to files under a given tree. If you have include_path entries that are not under that tree, you will get warnings.\r\n\r\nPrior to 1.10.1, we used fopen() in Zend_Loader::isReadable(). In this particular case, any directory on the include_path that is not under your specified basedir will simply be ignored, and it will only try those directories which are valid. In 1.10.1, to solve other issues that were manifesting, we now loop over the include_path manually and check paths using is_readable() -- which triggers the open_basedir restrictions.\r\n\r\nThe appropriate solution when using open_basedir is to ensure that all paths in your include_path are within the tree specified in that setting. This may mean copying libraries under your project directory.\r\n\r\nWe could potentially do checks on the open_basedir INI setting withing isReadable(), but I'm personally of the mind that its up to the developer to ensure appropriate configuration.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-15T06:24:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-15T06:24:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38466",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cnordlohne",
                        "name": "cnordlohne",
                        "displayName": "Christian Nordlohne",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Same here\r\n\r\nI Changed from 1.8.1 to 1.10.1\r\n\r\nWarning: is_readable() [function.is-readable]: open_basedir restriction in effect. File(\/usr\/share\/pear\/.\/views\/helpers\/Doctype.php) is not within the allowed path(s): (\/usr\/share\/php:\/usr\/local\/phpapps:\/usr\/local\/cgi:\/home\/demo) in \/usr\/local\/phpapps\/ZendFramework-1.10.1\/library\/Zend\/Loader.php on line 190\r\n\r\nso if I add \/usr\/share\/pear\/ to my open_basedir (via apache vhost) it works again but\r\n\r\n\/usr\/share\/pear\/.\/views\/helpers\/Doctype.php  is not a file under that destination\r\n\r\n\/usr\/local\/phpapps\/ZendFramework-1.10.1\/library\/Zend\/View\/Helper\/Doctype.php\r\n\/usr\/local\/phpapps\/ZendFramework-1.6.1\/library\/Zend\/View\/Helper\/Doctype.php\r\n\/usr\/local\/phpapps\/ZendFramework-1.7.1\/library\/Zend\/View\/Helper\/Doctype.php\r\n\/usr\/local\/phpapps\/ZendFramework-1.8.1\/library\/Zend\/View\/Helper\/Doctype.php\r\n\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cnordlohne",
                        "name": "cnordlohne",
                        "displayName": "Christian Nordlohne",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-15T07:57:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-15T07:57:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38685",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Max -- \/usr\/share\/php is probably in your global php.ini file, or defined in your vhost.\r\n\r\n@Christian: the PluginLoader searches across paths that are provided to it, and checks these against the include_path as well. Make sure that all paths you add to the PluginLoader are either absolute paths that are within your open_basedir setting, or on one or more include_paths (and that all include_paths are within your open_basedir setting).\r\n\r\nWe are unlikely to change the behavior of isReadable() back to use fopen(), as this was basically a bad hack, and clearly was circumventing security policies.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-23T10:12:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-23T10:12:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38756",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=avantis",
                        "name": "avantis",
                        "displayName": "Cristian Bichis",
                        "active": true
                    },
